<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>RADIATOR, REMOVE AND REPLACE - 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 7700 Models - RADIATOR AND COMPONENT REMOVAL - A/C
        condenser REPOSITION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="8">
        <title>A/C condenser REPOSITION</title>
        <para>The 7000 series cooling system is a front to back system. The A/C condenser is mounted forward of the
            charge air cooler. The A/C condenser must be repositioned to access the charge air cooler. The charge air
            cooler must be removed to access the radiator and frame assembly for removal.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the hood tilted and supported, disconnect hood stop cables.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the hinge cross bar mounting bracket (as applicable) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201008">Figure 8, Item 4</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the hinge cross bar mounting bolts and nuts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201008">Figure 8, Item 3</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the hood assembly forward on the hinge cross bar mounting plate (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201008">Figure 8, Item 2</hotlnk>) to access the lower A/C condenser mounting bolts
                (if applicable).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1201008" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1201008.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="240px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Hinge Cross Bar Mounting Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CHASSIS FRAME RAIL</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HINGE CROSS BAR MOUNTING PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HINGE CROSS BAR MOUNTING BOLTS AND LOCK NUTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HINGE CROSS BAR MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the chassis is equipped with air conditioning, the A/C condenser and mounting bracket
                must be relocated to access the charge air cooler, for removal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove lower A/C condenser mounting bolts from condenser mounting bracket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201009">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1201009" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1201009.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Condenser Mounting Bracket Bolt Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RADIATOR TOP RECIRCULATION SHIELD</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. A/C CONDENSER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the A/C condenser mounting bolts securing brackets to radiator frame.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the A/C condenser mounting bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201010">Figure 10, Item 2</hotlnk>) from the A/C condenser mounting brackets (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201010">Figure 10, Item 1</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove right recirculation shield, and remove hood cable stop if applicable.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201010" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/G1201010.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 10. A/C Condenser Mounting Bolt Removal (Passenger Side Shown)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. A/C CONDENSER MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>2. A/C CONDENSER MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate and remove stay rod lock nut and washer at radiator bracket, left side (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201011">Figure 11, Item 2</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1201011" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1201011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Stay Rod Removal (Driver Side Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. STAY ROD RADIATOR BRACKET AND STUD</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. STAY ROD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect A/C condenser lines from shroud (if applicable).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reposition the A/C condenser assembly and mounting brackets in a secured position out of the
                way (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201012">Figure 12 and 13, Item 2</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1201012" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1201012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Repositioning A/C Condenser</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CHARGE AIR COOLER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. A/C CONDENSER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>When repositioning, watch for kinking or severe bending of A/C condenser lines or hose (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1201013">Figure 13, Item 3</hotlnk>). Damage from kinking or severe bending may
                    require replacement of the A/C condenser lines.
                </para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1201013" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/G1201013.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 13. Repositioned A/C Condenser Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. CHARGE AIR COOLER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. A/C CONDENSER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>3. A/C CONDENSER LINES (HOSES)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If an external transmission cooler is supplied with the chassis, it must be removed prior to
                removing the charge air cooler.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the transmission cooler mounting bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201014">Figure 14, Item 6</hotlnk>) (lower mounting bolts shown) from the transmission
                mounting brackets.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the P-clip securing the transmission cooler lines to the radiator side frame (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201014">Figure 14, Item 2).</hotlnk>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201014" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/G1201014.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 14. Reposition External Transmission Cooler</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. RADIATOR SIDE FRAME (DRIVERS SIDE SHOWN)</callout1>
                <callout1>2. "P" CLIP</callout1>
                <callout1>3. RADIATOR GROUND WIRE</callout1>
                <callout1>4. LOWER CHARGE AIR COOLER MOUNTING BOLT AND BUSHING</callout1>
                <callout1>5. TRANSMISSION COOLER LINES</callout1>
                <callout1>6. TRANSMISSION COOLER MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                <callout1>7. A/C CONDENSER</callout1>
                <callout1>8. TRANSMISSION COOLER (EXTERNAL)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Relocate and secure the external transmission cooler assembly in an out of the way position
                (if applicable) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201015">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201015" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/G1201015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 15. External Transmission Cooler Relocated and Secured (if Equipped)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. TRANSMISSION COOLER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. TRANSMISSION COOLER MOUNTING BRACKETS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. TRANSMISSION COOLER LINES</callout1>
                <callout1>4. ENGINE BLOCK</callout1>
                <callout1>5. A/C COMPRESSOR</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
